The paper discusses the challenges of traditional software engineering practices in the context of Open Source Software (OSS) development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the socio-technical aspects of OSS development, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and software development (cs.SD) sub-categories.
